work retains full functionality most likely to lose data through collisions [5] (b) The LAN will connect to the internet through a router. The router has a public IPv6 address. (i) State why the router has a public IP address. ........................................................................................................................................... ..................................................................................................................................... [1] (ii) One difference between an IPv4 and IPv6 address is that the numbers in an IPv4 address are separated by full stops and in an IPv6 address they are separated by colons. Identify two other differences between an IPv4 and IPv6 address. 1 ........................................................................................................................................ ........................................................................................................................................... ........................................................................................................................................... 2 ........................................................................................................................................ ........................................................................................................................................... ........................................................................................................................................... [2]","libVersion":"0.3.2","langs":""}